@GRMIDX{{index="@HI{{hoshii}}" grammar="@HI{{hoshii}}"}}

<body>

<h1>@HI{{hoshii}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @HI{{@EM{{hoshii}}}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{hoshii}}}} is an @HI{{i}}-adjective that expresses a desire for something. The experiencer is marked by @HI{{ha}}
and the object that is desired is marked by @HI{{ga}}.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{car}}ga@EM{{hoshii}}desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I want a car.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
As @HI{{@EM{{hoshii}}}} is a strong adjective of emotion, the experiencer is usually the speaker. The experiencer can be
the listener if an interrogative form is used.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{child}}domoga@EM{{hoshii}}desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Do you want a child?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<br/><br/>

In most cases where a third person is the experiencer, @HI{{@EM{{hoshii}}}} 
will be used with <a href="grammar-garu.html">@HI{{garu}}</a> in the form @HI{{hoshigatteiru}}. There are exceptions where
@HI{{@EM{{hoshii}}}} can be used with a third person:
<ol>
<li> with a past tense

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{mo-risu}}haii@KT{{sutereo}}gahoshikatta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Maurice wanted a good stereo set.
  </td> </tr>
</table>

<li> in indirect speech

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{joi}}mohoshiito@KJ{{say}}tteiru.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Joy says she wants it too.
  </td> </tr>
</table>

<li> in explanatory situations

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{pamera}}ha@KT{{iyaringu}}gahoshiindesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      <em>(The explanation is that)</em> Pamela wants a pair of earrings.
  </td> </tr>
</table>

<li> in expressions of conjecture.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{furanshisu}}haude@KJ{{time^plot}}gahoshiirashii.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It seems that Francis wants a wristwatch.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>
</p>

